The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 19: The government has notified the revised foreign direct investment (FDI) guidelines in the telecom sector. The revised norms will allow telecom companies to appoint foreign CEOs with the approval of the home ministry. Companies can also have network access from remote areas. Both direct and indirect foreign investment in the licensee company shall be counted for the fdi ceiling, the guidelines said.

 Mumbai, April 19: ACC Ltds net profit rose to Rs 363.75 crore for the quarter ended March 31, 2007, compared with Rs 235.42 crore in the corresponding period last year. Good demand and rise in cement prices helped in the growth. 

 Mumbai, April 19: The Customs Excise and Service Tax Tribunal (CESTAT) has set aside a penalty of Rs 557 crore slapped by the Central Excise Haldia Commissionerate, Calcutta, on Tata Chemicals for using by-products of excisable goods while manufacturing non-excisable items.

 Calcutta, April 19: Calcutta High Court has appointed three special officers to help the Hindustan Motors management to bring vehicle components out of its factory premises at Uttarpara in Hooghly and hand it over to Tata Motors.




